research_municipality_step.notes: The City of Richardson, TX operates under a Council-Manager form of government. The City Council consists of a Mayor and six Council Members, all elected at-large for two-year terms. Council Members for Places 1-4 must reside in their respective areas, while the Mayor and Council Members for Places 5 and 6 are elected at-large without specific residency requirements beyond the city limits. The Mayor Pro Tem is chosen from among the elected council members.
